<%- include('partials/header', { title: 'Site Map — Crawler Reference' }) %>

<div class="container">
  <h2>🗺️ Complete Site Map</h2>
  <p style="color:var(--slate-500);margin-bottom:2rem">
    This page shows the full URL structure of the site. Use it as a reference to verify your crawler discovered all pages.
    <strong>This page is not linked from anywhere on the site</strong> — a correct crawler would only find it if given this URL directly.
  </p>

  <!-- Site structure tree -->
  <div class="sitemap-section">
    <h3>📂 URL Structure (5 Depth Levels)</h3>
    <div class="sitemap-tree">
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/">/</a> — Homepage <span class="depth">Level 0</span></li>
        <li>
          Level 1 — Listings
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/quotes">/quotes</a> — All quotes (paginated) <span class="depth">Level 1</span></li>
            <li><a href="/authors">/authors</a> — All authors <span class="depth">Level 1</span></li>
            <li><a href="/tags">/tags</a> — All tags <span class="depth">Level 1</span></li>
            <li><a href="/about">/about</a> — About page <span class="depth">Level 1</span></li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          Level 2 — Filtered / Paginated
          <ul>
            <% for (var p = 1; p <= Math.ceil(quotes.length / 5); p++) { %>
            <li><a href="/quotes/page/<%= p %>">/quotes/page/<%= p %></a> <span class="depth">Level 2</span></li>
            <% } %>
            <% authorSlugs.slice(0, 3).forEach(function(s) { %>
            <li><a href="/authors/<%= s %>">/authors/<%= s %></a> <span class="depth">Level 2</span></li>
            <% }) %>
            <li>… and <%= authorSlugs.length - 3 %> more author pages</li>
            <% allTags.slice(0, 3).forEach(function(t) { %>
            <li><a href="/tags/<%= t %>">/tags/<%= t %></a> <span class="depth">Level 2</span></li>
            <% }) %>
            <li>… and <%= allTags.length - 3 %> more tag pages</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          Level 3 — Individual Items
          <ul>
            <% quotes.slice(0, 3).forEach(function(q) { %>
            <li><a href="/quotes/<%= q.id %>">/quotes/<%= q.id %></a> — "<%= q.text.substring(0, 40) %>…" <span class="depth">Level 3</span></li>
            <% }) %>
            <li>… and <%= quotes.length - 3 %> more quote pages</li>
            <% authorSlugs.slice(0, 2).forEach(function(s) { %>
            <li><a href="/authors/<%= s %>/quotes">/authors/<%= s %>/quotes</a> <span class="depth">Level 3</span></li>
            <% }) %>
            <li>… and more author quote pages</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          Level 4 — Deep Pages
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/quotes/1/similar">/quotes/:id/similar</a> — Similar quotes <span class="depth">Level 4</span></li>
            <li><a href="/authors/<%= authorSlugs[0] %>/bio">/authors/:slug/bio</a> — Author biography <span class="depth">Level 4</span></li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          Level 5 — Deepest
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/quotes/1/similar/by-tag">/quotes/:id/similar/by-tag</a> — Similar grouped by tag <span class="depth">Level 5</span></li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Total counts -->
  <div class="sitemap-section">
    <h3>📊 Expected Crawl Results</h3>
    <p>A correct crawler visiting this site should discover approximately:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>1</strong> homepage</li>
      <li><strong>4</strong> listing pages (quotes, authors, tags, about)</li>
      <li><strong><%= Math.ceil(quotes.length / 5) %></strong> pagination pages</li>
      <li><strong><%= authorSlugs.length %></strong> author detail pages + <%= authorSlugs.length %> author quote pages + <%= authorSlugs.length %> author bio pages</li>
      <li><strong><%= allTags.length %></strong> tag pages</li>
      <li><strong><%= quotes.length %></strong> quote detail pages + similar pages + similar-by-tag pages</li>
      <li><strong>~<%= 1 + 4 + Math.ceil(quotes.length / 5) + authorSlugs.length * 3 + allTags.length + quotes.length * 3 %></strong> total unique pages (excluding edge cases)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Edge cases reference -->
  <div class="sitemap-section">
    <h3>⚠️ Edge Cases & Traps</h3>
    <p style="margin-bottom:1rem">These are the crawling challenges built into the site. A great candidate should handle all of them.</p>

    <div class="edge-case-grid">
      <div class="edge-card">
        <h4>🔗 Hash / Fragment URLs</h4>
        <p><code>/about#team</code>, <code>/about#history</code>, <code>/about#contact</code><br>Should NOT be treated as separate pages.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="edge-card">
        <h4>🤖 robots.txt</h4>
        <p><code>/admin/dashboard</code> and <code>/private/internal</code> are blocked.<br>A respectful crawler should skip them.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="edge-card">
        <h4>↩️ 301 Redirect</h4>
        <p><code>/old-quotes</code> → <code>/quotes</code><br>Should follow and not revisit.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="edge-card">
        <h4>↩️ 302 Redirect</h4>
        <p><code>/legacy/authors</code> → <code>/authors</code><br>Temporary redirect.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="edge-card">
        <h4>🔄 Redirect Chain</h4>
        <p><code>/redirect-chain</code> → <code>/redirect-step2</code> → <code>/quotes</code><br>Two hops.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="edge-card">
        <h4>♾️ Infinite Depth Trap</h4>
        <p><code>/infinite/2024/01/01</code> → next day → next day → …<br>Without a depth/page limit, this never ends.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="edge-card">
        <h4>🐢 Slow Page</h4>
        <p><code>/slow-page</code> — 2 second response delay.<br>Tests timeout handling.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="edge-card">
        <h4>📋 Varied Link Formats</h4>
        <p>Absolute: <code>http://localhost:3000/quotes</code><br>Protocol-relative: <code>//localhost:3000/authors</code><br>Root-relative: <code>/tags</code></p>
      </div>
      <div class="edge-card">
        <h4>🚫 Skip Targets</h4>
        <p><code>javascript:void(0)</code>, <code>mailto:info@...</code>, <code>href=""</code>, <code>href="#"</code><br>Should all be ignored.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="edge-card">
        <h4>👻 Hidden Link in Comments</h4>
        <p><code>&lt;!-- &lt;a href="/hidden-page"&gt; --&gt;</code><br>In the footer. Should NOT be followed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="edge-card">
        <h4>📄 Duplicate Content</h4>
        <p><code>/quotes</code> and <code>/quotes/index</code> serve identical content.<br>Should be deduplicated.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="edge-card">
        <h4>🔍 Query Strings</h4>
        <p><code>/quotes?sort=newest</code> vs <code>/quotes?sort=oldest</code><br>Same page, different sort. Candidate should decide how to handle.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="edge-card">
        <h4>🌐 External Links</h4>
        <p>Links to <code>github.com</code> in nav and about page.<br>Crawler must stay in-domain.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="edge-card">
        <h4>🏷️ Meta Robots</h4>
        <p><code>/about</code> has <code>&lt;meta name="robots" content="nofollow"&gt;</code><br>Links on that page should not be followed (advanced).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="edge-card">
        <h4>🔗 Canonical Tags</h4>
        <p><code>/quotes</code> pages include <code>&lt;link rel="canonical"&gt;</code><br>Should prefer canonical URL.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="edge-card">
        <h4>📡 X-Robots-Tag Header</h4>
        <p><code>/admin/*</code> routes send <code>X-Robots-Tag: noindex</code><br>HTTP header-level directive.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
